      "content": "<p>A review website needs more than sales-focused articles. It should help readers compare products, understand limitations and verify important terms before making a decision.</p><h2>Plan the information architecture</h2><p>Create a small number of clear categories. Use consistent URLs, breadcrumbs and internal links so readers can move between reviews and educational guides.</p><h2>Create a repeatable review template</h2><ul><li>Review basis and disclosure</li><li>Quick verdict</li><li>Product facts</li><li>Main features</li><li>Pros and cons</li><li>Pricing and upgrades</li><li>Who it is for</li><li>Alternatives</li><li>Final recommendation</li></ul><h2>Separate claims from evidence</h2><p>When a statement comes from a vendor sales page, label it as an advertised claim unless you have independently verified it.</p><h2>Improve internal linking</h2><p>Link product reviews to relevant tutorials, comparisons and category pages. Avoid adding unrelated links only to manipulate search engines.</p><h2>Maintain old reviews</h2><p>Prices, features and refund terms change. Add an updated date and periodically check your highest-traffic pages.</p>"
