      "content": "<p>PLR is not a single universal license. Every package can have different rules for editing, reselling, bundling, transferring rights and marketplace use.</p><h2>Read the delivered license</h2><p>Promotional headlines are not a substitute for the written license file. Save the license with your receipt and product files.</p><h2>Questions to ask</h2><ul><li>Can you edit the source files?</li><li>Can you sell the finished product?</li><li>Can you transfer PLR rights to customers?</li><li>Can you use the content on marketplaces?</li><li>Are there minimum-price rules?</li><li>Can you give the product away?</li></ul><h2>Check content quality</h2><p>Review accuracy, age, formatting, branding and source-file completeness. A large bundle is not necessarily valuable when most files require extensive updates.</p><h2>Plan your customization</h2><p>Replace branding, rewrite outdated sections and create a clear audience-specific offer. Selling the unchanged package may make it difficult to differentiate.</p>"
