      "content": "<p>An effective affiliate sequence helps readers understand a problem, evaluate options and make an informed decision. It should not rely on invented deadlines, fake testimonials or guaranteed results.</p><h2>Sequence structure</h2><ol><li>Introduce the problem and useful context.</li><li>Explain common mistakes or alternatives.</li><li>Present the product and review basis.</li><li>Discuss strengths, limitations and suitable users.</li><li>Remind readers to verify current pricing and terms.</li></ol><h2>Use accurate urgency</h2><p>Only mention a deadline when it is real and verifiable. Avoid countdown timers that reset for every visitor.</p><h2>Disclose affiliate relationships</h2><p>Place a clear disclosure where readers can see it before clicking the affiliate link.</p>"
